<!-- Please refer to CONTRIBUTING.md (https://github.com/fossology/FOSSologyUI/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md)
before creating the pull request to make sure you follow all the standards. -->

## Description

`/allRecentJobs` page UI is completed with a table featuring dynamic search and pagination. Also with a custom number of rows.

## Screenshot
![Screenshot from 2022-06-16 08-51-35](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/63705023/173984123-303e092a-9e45-458f-8a2f-a304c7bf26fc.png)

### Changes

A new package has been installed MDBreact (https://github.com/mdbootstrap/mdb-react-ui-kit)

## How to test

install the updated dependencies and run the server to visit the `/allRecentJobs` page

Fixes #222 

@shaheemazmalmmd  @GMishx @ag4ums  
Please do have a look
(https://help.github.com/articles/closing-issues-using-keywords/)

Signed-off-by: dushimsam <dushsam@gmail.com>

## Description

Added a new page for handling the upload of the CSV-license file.

### Changes

1. Added a new file [src/pages/Admin/Group/License/Import/index.jsx]
3. Introduced a new route in `src/Routes.jsx`
4. Introduced new API callers for the UI integration.

## How to test

1. Go to the project's main directory.
2. run command `npm start
3. Visit the page at `http://localhost:PORT/admin/license/import` 
4. The page should look as follows

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/66276301/188610009-73d56e61-e470-4f7c-b50f-10379f930752.png)

## Related Issue 
Closing #257

cc: @shaheemazmalmmd @GMishx

pr_body:
## Description introduces `jobs/all` endpoint. This endpoint returns all the jobs created by all the users. This endpoint only returns the jobs if the logged in user is an admin. Otherwise it returns an 403 error. ### Changes in `src/www/ui/api`: `index.php` is changed `Controllers/JobController.php` is changed. Also added the required docs for the new endpoint in the `openapi.yaml` file ## How to test make a call to the /jobs/all endpoint in a API testing application like Postman. ## Screenshots Admin response:
![Screenshot from 2022-07-13 20-00-05](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/63705023/178758890-fcaf56f8-c8bd-4cca-b887-237f07f21251.png) Other user's response:
![Screenshot from 2022-07-13 20-03-07](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/63705023/178759627-7f47153c-9fb9-4a6f-ad8b-19bce13f0296.png) Update to: #2253

        if (strcasecmp($copyFilepath['content'], $copy['content']) == 0) {
```", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 21, 1, 32, 28, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'GMishx', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 926176576, 'comment_body': "Note from [phpnet documentation](https://www.php.net/manual/en/function.array-push.php)
> Note: If you use array_push() to add one element to the array, it's better to use $array[] = because in that way there is no overhead of calling a function. 
```suggestion
            $copyrightContent[] = $copy['filePath'];
```", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 21, 1, 34, 23, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'GMishx', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 926177181, 'comment_body': 'Both, the inner and outer loop iterate on the same array and check if content of one is in other, which will always be true.

Is there any specific purpose for it?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 21, 1, 36, 12, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'GMishx', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 926178786, 'comment_body': "The action to set `$findings->setCopyright()` will set a class variable to `$copyrightContent` and the action `$findings->getCopyright()` will get that variable.

It is same as saying `$responseRow['filePath'] = $copyrightContent` without any overheads of class loading and function calls. Is there any additional benefit you are looking at which I missed?", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 21, 1, 40, 25, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'GMishx', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 926179596, 'comment_body': '```suggestion
            - "path/to/file1"
            - "path/to/file2"
```', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 21, 1, 42, 24, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'GMishx', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 926207519, 'comment_body': 'resolved', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 21, 2, 54, 36, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'soham4abc', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 926207632, 'comment_body': 'resolved', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 21, 2, 54, 51, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'soham4abc', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 926207678, 'comment_body': 'resolved', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 21, 2, 54, 59, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'soham4abc', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 926207776, 'comment_body': 'resolved', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 21, 2, 55, 12, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'soham4abc', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 926208104, 'comment_body': 'resolved', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 21, 2, 55, 56, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'soham4abc', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 926208153, 'comment_body': 'resolved', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 21, 2, 56, 5, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'soham4abc', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 926208238, 'comment_body': 'resolved', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 21, 2, 56, 17, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'soham4abc', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 926213924, 'comment_body': 'Unused variable.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 21, 3, 11, 47, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'GMishx', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 926217805, 'comment_body': 'Yes, I used this approach to get all the `filePath`s where the Copyright text is same. Iterating this nested loop does create the `copyrightContent` array for each Copyright text which is then further checked to exclude repeating texts.
The condition is only true when the current instance of the inner loop matches with the instance of the outer loop, which is not occurring every time.    ', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 21, 3, 22, 28, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'soham4abc', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 926217883, 'comment_body': 'resolved', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 21, 3, 22, 40, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'soham4abc', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 926221090, 'comment_body': 'Okay, got it.
Maybe there can be some way to optimize it still.

For example, File 1, 2 and 3 have copyright "Copyright 1". In first outer loop, you will merge file 1, 2 and 3 in inner loop and add it to the results array.
In second and third iteration of outer loop, again file 1, 2 and 3 will be merged but will not be added to the results array as the "Copyright 1" already exists there.

So there are some iterations wasted doing nothing.

Maybe think about optimizing it in a separate function, removing copyrights from the original list which are already used to combine the file paths?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 21, 3, 31, 17, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'GMishx', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 926222766, 'comment_body': 'Looking into it sir. Give me a bit of time. Will try to reduce the number of iterations wasted.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 21, 3, 35, 56, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'soham4abc', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 926235982, 'comment_body': 'Tried to optimize the nested loop structure in the latest push. Now the inner loop only executes only if the copyright does not exist in the response list itself. Thus no need to remove duplicates too.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 21, 4, 14, 55, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'soham4abc', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 926236340, 'comment_body': '@GMishx 
', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 21, 4, 15, 54, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'soham4abc', 'type': 'User'}]

pr_title: feat(ui): All jobs only accessible by admin
pr_body:
<!-- Please refer to CONTRIBUTING.md (https://github.com/fossology/FOSSologyUI/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md)
before creating the pull request to make sure you follow all the standards. -->

## Description

- All recent jobs is now only accessible  by admins ( Related with this back-end PR:  https://github.com/fossology/fossology/pull/2260 This needs to be merged first in order to avoid bugs.)
- MyRecentJobs page also implemented.

### Changes
Introduced a new API endpoint and used conditions for the header.

## How to test

Run compile the back-end after PR: ( https://github.com/fossology/fossology/pull/2260 ) is merged and run the server. Use Admin and non-Admin accounts to test out the jobs pages.


## Video 

[Screencast from 18-07-22 01:23:54 PM IST.webm](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/63705023/179469079-a1990390-aaf9-4958-a2d5-e34bb14271c6.webm)


Fixes #244

PTAL @GMishx @shaheemazmalmmd @Shruti3004

pr_title: fix(licenses): header fixed and limit for responses removed
pr_body:
<!-- Please refer to CONTRIBUTING.md (https://github.com/fossology/FOSSologyUI/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md)
before creating the pull request to make sure you follow all the standards. -->

## Description

Made changes in the request header of the API that was being called in order to show the licenses. Also enabled the field for edited responses. 

### Changes

Changes made in : `BrowserUploads/LicenseBrowser/index.jsx`

### Screenshots

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/63705023/180828544-f1f7687b-511e-4279-8606-b9628ecb1726.png)


## How to test

Start the server and visit a License browser page of a repository to see the updates.

PTAL: @GMishx @Shruti3004 @shaheemazmalmmd
